Boil a full #kettle{}. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British pork mince{240%g} and @sliced mushrooms{80%g}, ~{5-6%mins}.

Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with 0.5 tsp @salt{0.5%tsp}. Boil the @egg noodle nests{125%g}, ~{3-4%mins}. Once cooked, drain and run under cold water.

Next, reduce the heat of the frying pan to medium. Add the @ginger puree{15%g} and @coleslaw mix{120%g} and stir-fry, ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @miso paste{15%g}, @ketjap manis{25%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml} and @water{2%tbsp}.

Next, add the noodles to the frying pan. Toss to coat and simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Remove from the heat.

Share your noodles between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @crispy onions{1%sachet}.

Enjoy!